That is why I am proud to co-sponsor the National Flood Insurance Program Reauthorization and Reform (NFIP Re) Act of 2019.
Flooding is an issue we face in South Jersey almost every time it rains, and we need to tackle resiliency and mitigation efforts while extending coverage and keeping it affordable.

Today I am proud to stand with my fellow New Jersey members of the House and Senate to introduce bipartisan commonsense flood insurance reform.
